data.description:
Sugarcane
1.	Scientific name: Saccharum Officinarum
2.	Soil: loams & clay loams of Gangetic & other alluviums 
3.	Soil pH: 6.5 to 7.5 (< 6.5 add Lime. > 7.5 add Gypsum)
4.	Climate: Tropical & Sub-tropical crop
5.	Temperature: - Ideal temperature 28-32 C (above 45C reduce tillering)
	Germination stage- 30 to 34°C. 
	Vegetative growth- 20-30°C.
	Ripening stage- 12-15°C
6.	Rainfall: 75-120 cm
7.	Relative Humidity: 70-85%(growth)& 55-75%(Ripening) is ideal
8.	Crop season: Kharif crop
9.	Sowing season: Pre seasonal: 15 Oct-30 Nov, Adsali: 15 july-15 August, Suru: 15 Dec- 15 
10.	Seed rate:  25,000 to 30,000  budded setts per hectares(MP)
11.	Sett Treatment: 15 minutes in 0.2% Carbendazim (200 g in 100 litre of water) before sowing
12.	Preparation of field:- Plough the land 1 or 2 times based on soil type
13.	Method of sowing: Deep furrow, Trench methods, Ring pit method, Paired row method and Furrow method
14.	Spacing: 90cm row spacing 
15.	Fertilizer doze: 120:56:56 N: P: K kg/acre
	15 Days after planting Urea- 100 Kg, Single super phosphate 172 kg, Muriate of potash- 48 kg
	130 Days after planting Urea- 50 Kg, Single super phosphate 75 kg, Muriate of potash- 15 kg
16	Macro Nutrient application: Sardar Bio-chemical NPK 20:20:20 @ 1kg/acre or Nagarjuna Peak
17	Micro-Nutrients: PI Biovita-X @ 250ml/acre or Quantis -@ 350ml/acre (Syngenta )  or Nutrozen -@ 300ml/acre  (Crystal ) or Agromin Gold -250ml/acre ( Aries) or Aura Xl -250 ml/acre  ( Coromandal A) Or Rubitrol -250gm /acre (Zytex)
18	Irrigation: 6-8 irrigations
19	Weed management
	Narrow leaf: Dhanuka Sempra @ 200 ml/acre or Dhanuka Weedmar Super 2,4-D Amine Salt 58% SL @ 400ml/acre by foliar application
	Narrow & Broad leaf: Syngenta Calaris Xtra 27.5SC (Atrazine + Mesotrion)@ 140ml/acre 
20	Crop Protection
	Diseases: Red rot in sugarcane, Rust,. Yellow Leaf Diseases, Sett Rot, Smut 
Control: Sygenta Tespa Propiconazole 13.9% + Difenconazole 13.9% EC@ 200ml/acre by spray or Sygenta Alika Thiamethoxam (12.6%) + Lambdacyhalothrin (9.5%) ZC @ 150ml/acre by spray
	Pest: Termites, Early shoot borer, Internode borer, Top Borer, Sugarcane Wooly Aphid, White Fly, Mealy bug, White Grub, Ratoon stunting 
Control: Basf Vesticor Chlorantraniliprol 18.5 % SC @150ml/acre
21	Harvest: 330 to 360 Days after planting, done by cutting the canes at ground level
22	Yield: 69.4 t/ha

Paddy
1.	Scientific name: Oryza sativa
2.	Soil: loam to sandy loam to clay loam, but clay loam soils with good water retention capacity
3.	Soil pH: 5.5
4.	Climate: Subtropical type, high temperature, high humidity 
5.	Temperature: -  25 degree Celsius
6.	Rainfall: 100 cm
7.	Crop season: Kharif season
8.	Sowing season: Second fortnight of June is the optimum time for realizing higher yields
9.	Seed rate:  70-90 kg/ha for drilling and 100-120 kg/ha for broadcasting 
10.	Seed Treatment: 1) Tricoderma @ 125gm per 25kg seed 2) 75gm thiram or 50gm carbendazim in 8-10lt water to treat 25kg seed
11.	Preparation of field:- 2-3 ploughing are required to prepare the soil, leveling should be followed for ensuring adequate crop stand and finally achieving higher yield
12.	Method of sowing: Direct seedling, Transplanting 
13.	Spacing: 20x15cm or 20x10cm 
14.	Depth : 3-4cm
15.	Transplant 2-3 plant per hill for better yield
16.	Time of transplanting: i)Early and medium maturing varieties 3rd week of June to mid of July ii) long duration and dwarf can be transplanted upto last week of July(20-22 days old nursery is consider good for transplanting)
17.	Fertilizer doze: Farm yard manure @ 10 t/ha or green manure @ 5 t/ha 2-3 weeks in advance, 
	High Yielding Early Maturing NPK @ 120:60:60
	High Yielding Medium Maturity NPK @ 150:60:60
	Scented paddy (dwarf) NPK @ 120:60:60
18.	Split fertilizer application: Half the dose of nitrogen and full dose of phosphorus and potash before transplanting & remaining dose of nitrogen should be used in two instalments 1st at the time of tillering and the 2nd at the time of emergence of ears as top dressing
19.	Irrigation: Irrigate the crop at tillering , ear emergence, flowering and grain filling stage
20.	Major weeds: dicot and monocot 
	Major dicot weeds are: Chenopodium album, Fumaria parviflora, Cirsium arvense, Anagallis arvensis etc
	Monocot weeds include: Phalaris minor, Avena fatua (wild oat), Cyperus rotundus, Cynodon dactylon 
21.	Weed Control
	Pre-emergence herbicides: Butachlor, Thibencarb, Pretilachlor @ 1.0-1.5 kg/ha and Anilofos @ 0.4 kg/ha 
	Post-emergence herbicides: Propanil, 2,4-D and MCPA @ 0.5 kg/ha
22.	Crop Protection
	Diseases: : Sheath blight, Bacterial blight, false smut
	Pest: Root weevil, leaf roller, husk insect, hispa , bunka insect, stem borer, green, brown , white hoppers, Gandhi bug, and army worm
23.	Harvest: 30-35 days after flowering when stalks still remain green to avoid grain shedding
24.	Harvest moisture %: Around 20 per cent
25.	Yield: average yields vary from 4-5 tons/ha during kharif
26.	Storage: Store at 10 to 12 % moisture.
